<HEADLINE> Russia, Ukraine Reaffirm Strategic Partnership </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, September 19 (Xinhua) -- The presidents of Russia and
Ukraine Saturday reaffirmed their aim to develop bilateral
relations of strategic partnership, mutual respect and good
neighborliness.
</P>
<P>
In a joint communique signed here after their two-day informal
summit, Russian President Boris Yeltsin and his Ukrainian
counterpart, Leonid Kuchma, said they remain committed to all
previously signed bilateral agreements.
</P>
<P>
They also discussed measures to deal with the current crisis
besetting both countries and instructed their governments to form
a joint anti-crisis task force as soon as possible.
</P>
<P>
According to press reports, Yeltsin and Kuchma praised the two
countries' cooperation in international aerospace projects such as
the creation of a European modification of the An-70 plane.
</P>
<P>
The two sides also reached an agreement on Russia's
participation in completing two power-generation units at
Ukraine's Rovno and Khmelnitsk nuclear power plants and Russia's
loans for these projects in 1999, the Itar-Tass news agency
reported. 
</P>
</TEXT>
