<HEADLINE> S. Africa Condemns Killing of Iranian Diplomats </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, September 19 (Xinhua) -- South Africa Saturday
condemned the recent killing of eight Iranian diplomats and one
journalist by Afghanistan's anti-government Taliban forces.
</P>
<P>
In a statement, the South African Foreign Affairs Department
said the killing of diplomats was seen as an unacceptable breach
of the provisions of the Vienna Convention on diplomatic
relations.
</P>
<P>
The South African government supported calls for a thorough
investigation into the tragic events, the statement said, adding
that perpetrators of the bloody incident must be brought to
justice.
</P>
<P>
The nine Iranian innocent people were killed on August 8 in
the city of Mazar-i-Sharif, Afghanistan.
</P>
<P>
The South African government also called on all parties to the
conflict in Afghanistan to cease hostilities, exercise restraint,
observe international accepted norms of human rights and pursue a
solution to the conflict through peaceful means and dialog.
</P>
</TEXT>
