<HEADLINE> Rwanda's War Against Congo (K) Possible: Minister </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, September 19 (Xinhua) -- Visiting Rwandan
Education Minister Joseph Karemera said Saturday that his
government did not rule out the possibility of engaging in war
against the Democratic Republic of Congo (DRC).
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a press conference here, Karemera said the
genocide committed against Tutsi people in Congo (K) must be
stopped.
</P>
<P>
Rwanda, a Hutu-dominated country, has been ruled by Tutsi
people since July, 1994 as the Rwandan Patriotic Front guerrillas
swooped down from Uganda on the country to stop the genocide of
half a million Tutsis and Hutu moderates.
</P>
<P>
Soldiers of Congo's ethnic Tutsis rebelled in early August
against President Laurent Kabila and Congo accused Rwanda of
invading to back the rebellion.
</P>
<P>
Karemera denied the allegations that Rwandan soldiers were
involved in the Congo crisis which has lasted since August 2.
</P>
<P>
The Rwandan minister also criticized Zimbabwe, Angola and
Namibia, who have deployed troops in support of the Congolese
government headed by President Kabila, saying that they should
reconsider their decision. 
</P>
</TEXT>
