<HEADLINE> Singapore Prime Minister Visits U.S., Chile </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, September 19 (Xinhua) -- Singapore Prime Minister
Goh Chok Tong has left here for a working visit to the United
States from September 19 to 26 and an official visit to Chile from
September 30 to October 1, according to an announcement of
Singapore's Prime Minister's Office Saturday.
</P>
<P>
During his stay in Washington, the Prime Minister will meet
with U.S. President Bill Clinton and several U.S. Cabinet
Secretaries and key members of the U.S. Congress, attend an
interactive session to be hosted by the Chairman of the U.S.
Senate Foreign Relations Sub-Committee on East Asian and Pacific
Affairs, meet leading corporate representatives at events to be
separately hosted by the U.S. - ASEAN Business Council and the
U.S. Chamber of Commerce, and address the U.S. Chamber of Commerce
on September 22.
</P>
<P>
In New York, the Prime Minister will deliver a speech at the
Asia Society Annual dinner on September 25.
</P>
<P>
His trip to Chile is a reciprocal visit after Chilean President
Eduardo Frei visited Singapore in November 1996. During his stay
in the South American country, Goh Chok Tong will hold talks with
Frei, meet Chilean political and corporate leaders at several
events organized in his honor, and deliver a lecture at the
University of Chile.
</P>
<P>
From September 27-29 and October 2-6, 1998, the Prime Minister
will have private vacation in the U.S..
</P>
<P>
During his absence, Singapore Deputy Prime Minister Lee Hsien
Loong will be acting Prime Minister from September 20-27, 1998 and
October 2-7 , 1998, while Deputy Prime Minister and Minister for
Defense Tony Tan Keng Yam will be acting Prime Minister from
September 28 to October 1. 
</P>
</TEXT>
