<HEADLINE> Fighting Breaks out in Liberian Capital </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, September 19 (Xinhua) -- Small arms and heavy machine
gun fire broke out in Liberian capital Monrovia Friday night and
raged on till early Saturday morning, an agency report from
Abidjan in neighboring Cote d'Ivoire has said.
</P>
<P>
The report quoted Monrovia residents as saying that the
fighting was around the stronghold of ethnic Krahn clan opposed
to President Charles Taylor.
</P>
<P>
The fighting site is about a kilometer from the Mamba Point
diplomatic enclave, the residents said, adding that there was no
immediate information on any casualties.
</P>
<P>
"Traffic was immediately affected with a lot of people seeking
refuge in Mamba Point on Friday night," said a resident.
</P>
<P>
The residents in suburban Monrovia said that roads leading to
the city center have been blocked. 
</P>
