<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD -- At least 16 people were killed and 40 others
injured Sunday in a rocket attack on the Afghan capital of Kabul,
Afghanistan's Bakhtar news agency reported. The report said that
the rocket attack happened at 2:30 local time, and it is carried
out by the forces of opposition commander Ahmed Shah Masood. The
rocket hit a residential area called Khairkhana, and six women
from the same family were among the dead, the report quoted
residents as saying, adding several children were injured in the
rocket attack which hit several houses.
</P>
<P>
Earlier Sunday a rocket landed on wasteland near the Kabul
airport but caused no casualties, residents said. Sunday's rocket
attack is the most fierce in a month since the Taliban captured
the central Afghan province of Bamyan. (Afghanistan-Rocket Attack)
