<HEADLINE> 16 Killed, 40 Injured in Rocket Attack on Kabul </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, September 20 (Xinhua) -- At least 16 people were
killed and 40 others injured Sunday afternoon in a rocket attack
on the Afghan capital of Kabul, Afghanistan's Bakhtar news agency
reported.
The report said that the rocket attack happened at 2:30 local
time, and it is carried out by the forces of opposition commander
Ahmed Shah
Masood.
The rocket hit a residential area called Khairkhana, and six
women from the same family were among the dead, the report quoted
residents as saying, adding several children were injured in the
rocket attack which hit several houses.
</P>
<P>
Initial reports has said nine people were killed.
Earlier Sunday a rocket landed on wasteland near the Kabul
airport but caused no casualties, residents said.
Sunday's rocket attack is the most fierce in a month since the
Taliban captured the central Afghan province of Bamyan. 
</P>
