<HEADLINE> Glorious Life of Yang Shangkun (12) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Yang firmly implemented the strategic change in the guiding
ideology of army building, and policy measures in reforming the
system of the armed forces, working for lean and mean troops,
introducing a new system of military ranks and various laws and
regulations, improving political and ideological work,
strengthening the building of the grass-roots units, establishing
the armed police forces, strengthening logistical support,
readjusting the system of national defense industries and
accelerating the development of sophisticated state-of-the-art
weaponry, thus guaranteeing that the PLA embarks on a road of
building a modern and regular revolutionary armed forces at peace
time.
</P>
<P>
Yang acted in accordance with the correct analysis and
judgement of the CPC Central Committee concerning the
international situation and actively implemented Deng Xiaoping's
guiding ideology on military modernization in the new period.
</P>
<P>
He stressed that the whole army should conscientiously study
and understand Deng Xiaoping Theory on building socialism with
Chinese characteristics.
</P>
<P>
He noted that the Party and state have shifted the work focus
to economic construction during the new period, and said the armed
forces should firmly support the government in concentrating
efforts on economic construction.
</P>
<P>
He stressed the PLA should strengthen national defense
construction, maintain its status as a people's army, develop a
high-level combat effectiveness and remain on high state of
military preparedness and provide security guarantee for the
national economic construction, reform and opening up.
</P>
<P>
He pointed out that army building should center on the military
modernization, take combat effectiveness as the standard and
highlighted the need for strengthening military training.
</P>
<P>
He stressed the need for studying and finding solutions to
maritime issues, the need for safeguarding the rights and
interests of the nation's territorial waters and strengthening
actual control of the nation's islands and coastlines in order to
defend the state sovereignty and territorial integrity.
</P>
