<HEADLINE> University of Science, Technology Celebrates 40th Anniversary </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HEFEI, September 20 (Xinhua) -- Chinese University of Science
and Technology (CUST), a cradle of scientists and researchers,
celebrated its 40th anniversary today.
</P>
<P>
More than 1,400 alumni returned to their Alma Mater in Hefei,
capital of east China's Anhui Province, to attend the ceremony
together with nearly 10,000 teachers and students.
</P>
<P>
The celebration drew 60 presidents of well-known universities
in China and overseas, more than 50 academicians of the Chinese
Academy of Sciences and the Chinese Academy of Engineering, as
well as scientists from key Chinese and overseas research
institutes.
</P>
<P>
Top Chinese leaders Jiang Zemin and Li Peng wrote inscriptions
of congratulation for the university.
</P>
<P>
Founded on September 20, 1958, in Beijing and moved to Hefei in
1970, CUST has trained more than 40,000 scientists and researchers
and has become one of the importment research centers in China.
</P>
<P>
The university currently has 11 institutes and 56 majors, and
employs 1,600 teachers and nearly 400 professors.
</P>
<P>
More than 40 academic reports will be delivered by scientists
from the Chinese Academy of Sciences and Chinese Academy of
Engineering during the event.  
</P>
</TEXT>
