<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Year's Official Cotton Purchasing Prices Unchanged </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 20 (Xinhua) -- The government-set cotton
purchasing prices in 1998 will remain unchanged so as to protect
the interests of cotton growers, according to a national
conference on cotton production, which closed on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
On April 1 this year, the government lowered the price from the
previous 700 yuan per 50 kg to 650 yuan per kg, with the minimum
price set at 617.5 yuan per 50 kg, for province-level areas except
for the Xinjiang Uygur Autonomous Region.
</P>
<P>
For Xinjiang, the official price was lowered to 600 yuan per 50
kg, from the previous 630 yuan, while the regional government was
authorized to set its own range of price fluctuations.
</P>
<P>
State-run supply and marketing cooperatives are the sole
cotton purchaser, processor and dealer in the country.
</P>
<P>
This year, the acreage of cotton fields stands at 4.43 million
ha., 133,333 ha. less than last year. Summer floods across the
country damaged the crop on some 233,333 ha. and, thus, are
expected to reduce the total output.
</P>
<P>
This year's cotton output is estimated at slightly lower than
last year's 4.3 million tons. 
</P>
</TEXT>
