<HEADLINE> Yingxian County Opens Liao Dynasty Street </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TAIYUAN, September 20 (Xinhua) -- Yingxian County in north
China's Shanxi Province recently opened a Liao Dynasty Street to
display the architectural styles of China's Liao Dynasty
(916-1125 A.D.).
</P>
<P>
Structures along the street, which is 340 meters long and 60
meters wide, have total floor space of 12,000 square
meters. Buildings along the street present the rich cultural
features of the Liao Dynasty.
</P>
<P>
The street will features a famous wooden pagoda built during
the Liao Dynasty.
</P>
<P>
The county is currently engaged in an extensive effort to
develop tourism resources. Plans call for the construction of a
wooden pagoda square, a pagoda park and the partial restoration of
a wall built during the Liao Dynasty.  
</P>
