<HEADLINE> Holyfield Wins 12-round Bout against Bean </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, September 19 (Xinhua) -- Evander Holyfield knocked
down Vaughn Bean in the 10th round to win a unanimous decision in
Atlanta on Saturday night.
</P>
<P>
In front of 41,357 audience in the Georgia Dome, Holyfield
took sidestep against Bean and flung him into the ropes with his
left arm before landing a heavy right to the head of his opponent
in the late 10th round.
</P>
<P>
"He hit me when I was down," said the 25-year-old Bean said,
"The ref didn't do his job. I know I was on his home turf. He
hit me right on the temple. The ref could have stepped in."
</P>
<P>
"I've got to take advantage of every opportunity I get,
because he's a good fighter," said Holyfield, who will be 36 on
Octocer 19. "I just turned and hit him. That's part of the boxing
game."
</P>
<P>
Judge Duane Ford of Nevada scored it 116-111, while Al DeVito
and Leroy Brown, each had it 117-111 for Holyfield.
</P>
<P>
Holyfield's next fight is expected to be a mandatory WBA
defense against Henry Akinwande of Britain.
</P>
<P>
The turnout for Holyfield's third title defense in his
hometown was the biggest since 70,000 watched Muhammad Ali
regained the undisputed heavyweight title from Leon Spinks in
September 1978.
</P>
<P>
With the win, Holyfield recorded his 36th victory against
three defeats, including 25 knockouts, while Bean lost for only
the second time against 32 victories including 25 knockouts.
</P>
</TEXT>
