At a meeting with Mejdani, Polish Foreign Minister Bronislaw
Geremek said, "We have come to convey to you the full confidence
of the international community in your irreplaceable role in the
present situation."
</P>
<P>
Bronislaw, who is the current chairman of the Organization for
Security and Cooperation in Europe (OSCE), is on a visit to
Albania at the head of a European delegation.
</P>
<P>
Daniel Tarchys, the secretary-general of the Council of Europe
and a member of the delegation, said, "We are confident that your
moral authority at home and abroad will influence the restoration
of the sense of national conciliation and unity."
</P>
<P>
According to the presidential press office, the president
briefed the delegation on the situation in Albania and his efforts
to bring political forces to the round-table talks.
</P>
<P>
"I have asked the opposition political parties to denounce acts
of violence against state institutions and to disassociate
themselves from the practice of arming the militants," the
president said.
</P>
<P>
He said that the problem of Kosovo is a very important issue
and the international community should follow it closely with
adequate measures.
</P>
<P>
He called for fast and extensive actions to help Kosovo
refugees in Albania. Large numbers of refugees fled to the
Albanian border town of Shkoder in the past few days. 
</P>
