July this year recorded a surplus of 9 million U.S. dollars,
according to the Central Bank (CB) Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Exports for July stood at 511 million dollars while imports
were valued at 502 million dollars.
</P>
<P>
This was the first time in the past 30 months that exports
exceed imports in a single month in the country, CB sources told
Xinhua.
