Galan and Felipe Torres held a meeting with representatives of the
Senate's Human Rights Commission in the northeast state of
Antioquia, where the mayors were kidnapped.
</P>
<P>
The release was described as "a show of good will" when the two
ELN leaders and the National Peace Council (CNP) representatives
formed a preparatory commission on Monday for a "National
Convention," a condition raised by the ELN for future peace talks.
</P>
<P>
The "National Convention" was one of the points agreed on July
15 in Mainz, Germany, after a three-day meeting between the ELN,
the second biggest guerrilla group in the country, and the
Colombian civil society.
</P>
<P>
The ELN also agreed to release Senator Carlos Espinosa next
Tuesday, who was abducted in early August, and four other mayors
will be freed at an undetermined site east of Antioquia. 
