<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Indonesia's Javanese Eagle on Brink of Extinction </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, September 20 (Xinhua) -- Dwindling natural forests
pose one of the threats to Indonesia's Javanese eagle whose
population is now estimated at only 250 to 300, Antara News Agency
reported on Sunday, quoting a conservation group.
</P>
<P>
Rampant hunting and illegal trading have also hindered the
conservation of the endangered birds, the Working Committee for
Javanese Eagle Conservation said in a press release.
</P>
<P>
In 1997 alone, a number of non-governmental organizations found
at least 22 Javanese eagles traded at bird markets in various
cities on Java island, the committee said.
</P>
<P>
The illegal but lucrative trade in Javanese eagles has
encouraged the hunting of the bird species.
</P>
<P>
"This is one of the threats to the conservation of the national
animal," the committee said.
</P>
<P>
Javanese eagles were first found in 1870, and named after its
discoverer M. Bartels Sr.
</P>
<P>
Many people keep the Javanese eagle as a pet because this bird
species is also known as "Garuda" (mythical bird).
</P>
<P>
According to the Red Data Book issued by the Union for
Conservation of Nature and Natural Resources, Javanese eagles are
endangered bird species with the high risk of extinction. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980920.0145 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-09-20 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Manzhouli Customs Strengthens Anti-smuggling Efforts </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HOHHOT, September 20 (Xinhua) -- The Customs Office in the
border city of Manzhouli achieved great progress in
anti-smuggling efforts during the first half of this year.
</P>
<P>
Recent statistics show that customs officers concluded 44
smuggling cases between January and June, with related
investigations leading to the confiscation of smuggled goods
valued at 6.13 million yuan (738,000 US dollars).
</P>
<P>
Local customs officials noted that the majority of smuggled
items involved illicit drugs and pornographic publications. Over
10,000 tablets of controlled substances were confiscated during
the period.
</P>
<P>
The office witnessed an increase in the number of smuggled cars
and motor bikes, with 16 vehicles and 17 motor bikes confiscated
during the period.
</P>
<P>
Customs officers arrested an increasing number of people in
possession of illegal firearms, with confiscated items including
four handguns, 47 rounds of ammunition and one tear gas cannister.
</P>
