<HEADLINE> Bureau to Report Zhujiang River Water Quality </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, September 20 (Xinhua) -- The water quality for the
Zhujiang River, one of China's major rivers, will be reported on a
regular basis, according to the local Water Resources Protection
Bureau.
</P>
<P>
The bureau has coordinated the water quality monitoring program
since April this year. The water quality has been tested every two
months, with 75 percent samples qualifying a medium levels.
</P>
<P>
The monitoring center in the Zhujiang River valley has
initiated a plan to dispatch personnel to various sites in the
river valley to collect samples and guarantee the validity of
related reports.  
