<HEADLINE> Ecuador, Peru Reach Border Accord </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
RIO DE JANEIRO, September 19 (Xinhua) -- Ecuador and Peru have
reached a peace accord to end their border disputes, the "Folha de
Sao Paulo" newspaper reported Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The agreement will be announced in Brasilia on September 28 by
Brazilian President Fernando Henrique Cardoso, Ecuadoran President
Jamil Mahuad and Peruvian President Alberto Fujimori.
</P>
<P>
Under the agreement, Ecuador and Peru accepted to turn the
disputed territory into natural parks and historical monuments.
</P>
<P>
Mahuad and Fujimori plan to meet Cardoso in Brasilia, the
capital of Brazil, on September 27 and 28 to put a final touch on
the accord.
</P>
<P>
The border dispute between Ecuador and Peru led to military
confrontation in 1941, 1981 and 1995. 
