<HEADLINE> Hingis Gives Swiss 1-1 Tie with Spain </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GENEVA, September 19 (Xinhua) -- Martina Hingis defeated
Conchita Martinez in straight sets Saturday, helping Switzerland
to draw Spain 1-1 after the first day's play of the Fed Cup Final.
</P>
<P>
Hingis won the second singles in straight sets with an identi
cal score of 6-4 to even the best-of-5 tie after French Open
champ Arantxa Sanchez-Vicario won the first singles over Patty
Schnyder 6-2, 3-6, 6-2.
</P>
<P>
"I felt great today, and I had a solid win," said Hingis,
winner of four Grand Slams.
</P>
<P>
Hingis and Martinez traded breaks twice in the back-and-forth
first set before the Swiss capitalized on a second break point in
the 10th game to win the set.
</P>
<P>
In the second set, Hingis broke to lead 4-2 and had a double
break, double set point at 5-3 but lost the next four points to
allow Martinez to get back on serve.
</P>
<P>
Hingis stormed back in the next game, breaking the Spaniard at
love to take the match.
</P>
<P>
In the reversed singles, Hingis will face Sanchez-Vicario
against whom the Swiss teenager has a 7-1 record including
victories in their last six meetings.
</P>
<P>
In the first singles of the day, Sanchez-Vicario dominated the
first set of her match against Swiss teenager Schynder who
double-faulted on break point to give the Spaniard a 3-1
advantage and a second break point to go ahead 5-1.
</P>
<P>
In the second set, Schnyder broke back twice to even the score
2-2 and 4-4 before taking the final game to her credit.
</P>
<P>
The 19-year-old Swiss broke Sanchez-Vicario to open the final
set but failed to stop the Spaniard from rallying back to lead
4-2 and 5-2 to win the crucial set. 
</P>
