<P>
England captain Alan Shearer scored twice, to add to the
couple he hit in a 4-0 home win over Southampton last Saturday,
as the Magpies continued their return to form since Gullit
replaced former manager Kenny Dalglish in late August.
</P>
<P>
The result lifted Newcastle's points tally to eight from six ga
mes, six points behind leaders Aston Villa, who drew 0-0 at Leeds
United. Liverpool slipped to third on 11 points after a 3-3 draw
with Charlton at Anfield where Robbie Fowler marked his return
from injury with two goals for the home side.
</P>
<P>
