<HEADLINE> Top Seed Clavet to Vie against Pasquale in Romanina Open </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, September 19 (Xinhua) -- Top seed Francisco Clavet
of Spain on Saturday won his semifinal to vie for the Romanian
Open title against unseeded Frenchman Arnaud Di Pasquale.
</P>
<P>
The Spaniard overcame a first-set deficit to defeat compatriot
Albert Portas 3-6, 6-0, 6-2 to reach the final of the 350,000
U.S. dollars Romanian Open.
</P>
<P>
In the other semifinal, unseeded Di Pasquale eliminated
Romanian Adrian Voinea 6-3, 2-6, 7-5 in a battle of baseline
efforts.
</P>
<P>
From 1-1, Di Pasquale capitulated on a series of unforced
errors by Voinea on the clay court.
</P>
<P>
Both matches were delayed several hours by heavy rain. 
</P>
</TEXT>
